{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἱππ-άζομαι</b>, <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> <i>future</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> ἱππασεῖται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Dialexeis 5th c.BC” 6.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>drive horses, drive a chariot</b>, Ἀντίλοχ᾽, ἀφραδέως ἱππάζεαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.426 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; later, <b>ride</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.114, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 17, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 15, etc.; ἱ. ἐφ᾽ ἵππων 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.110; ἵππῳ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 10.1: _metaphorically_, ἁ ξυσμὰ ἐκ ποδὸς εἰς κεφαλὰν ἱππάζεται 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 53:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —rare in <i>active</i>, ἱππάσαι πῶλον cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.182. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, of the horse, <b>to be ridden</b> or <b>driven</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ion” 540e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>to be broken in for riding</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 3.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i> loci, ἱππάζεσθαι χώραν <b>ride over</b> a country, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Camillus” 23; τὰς ὁδούς 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 13.88. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7725","accentedUnicode":"ἱππάζομαι","shortDef":"to ride a horse","mediumDef":"to ride a horse","stepGloss":"to ride a horse","stepTransliteration":"hippazomai","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}